    <title type="text">COL - Latin Spellchecker </title>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<a
      href="http://drouizig.org/index.php/en/binviou-en/correttore-ortografico-di-latino/250-en-col-latin-spellchecker"><span
      style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family: inherit;">COL - Latin
      Spellchecker&nbsp;</span></span></a><br /><blockquote
      class="tr_bq"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family:
      inherit;"><img alt="http://drouizig.org/images/stories/latinscreen2.png" class="decoded"
      height="263" src="http://drouizig.org/images/stories/latinscreen2.png" width="320" />
      </span></span></blockquote><blockquote class="tr_bq"><span
      style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-family:
      inherit;"></span></span><span style="font-size: small;"><span
      style="font-family: inherit;"></span></span><span style="font-size:
      small;"><span style="font-family: inherit;"></span></span><span
      style="font-size: x-small;">Correcteur Orthographique de Latin<br /><span
      style="font-family: inherit;"></span><span style="font-family:
      inherit;"></span><span style="font-family: inherit;"></span>Correttore
      Ortografico di Latino<span style="font-family: inherit;"><span style="font-weight:
      normal;"><span style="line-height:
      1.3em;">&nbsp;</span></span></span></span><br /><span
      style="font-size: x-small;"><span style="font-family: inherit;"><span
      style="font-weight: normal;"><span style="line-height: 1.3em;">Corrector Ortográfico
      de Latín</span></span></span></span></blockquote><blockquote
      class="tr_bq"><span style="font-size: x-small;">COL (Correcteur Orthographique de
      Latin) is a free tool providing assistance to check the spelling of a Latin text. Available for
      Microsoft Word, LibreOffice, OpenOffice.org and AbiWord, it includes a dictionary of about
      400,000 Latin forms (classical and medieval Latin).</span><br /><br />
      <span style="font-size: x-small;">To best match the different practices, COL is
      configurable: the user can select a particular spelling (how to represent diphthongs, vowels u
      and i...). It works exactly like spellcheckers of other languages: when a word is not in the
      dictionary, it is underlined in red.</span><br /><br /> <span
      style="font-size: x-small;">This spellchecker is obviously not intended to be exhaustive,
      nor it wants to "normalize" the spelling of Latin. It was created primarily as an aid to save
      time and facilitate the work of all those who need to understand Latin texts (for the
      transcription of manuscripts, for example), but also to fix correct Latin texts scanned and
      processed by OCR, usually with many faults.</span><br /><br /> <span
      style="font-size: x-small;">In order to get in touch with our software, a good
      <em>'How To'</em> written in Latin language <a
      href="http://de-tribulis.blogspot.com/p/enchiridion-correctoris-orthographiae.html">can be
      read here</a>. Note that the Latinists from the Vatican City are using our software since
      its early releases.</span><br /> <span style="font-size: x-small;">Want to
      share feedback, problems ? <a
      href="http://www.facebook.com/home.php#/group.php?gid=69714184256">Join us on
      Facebook</a>! Or may you have any question, please contact us at: <a
      href="mailto:drouizig@drouizig.org">drouizig@drouizig.org</a> (important, please put
      [COL] in your message subject).</span></blockquote>]]></content>
